# Progressive unlock: keep Day 3-5 pages out of the repo for now so only
# Day 1-2 content is visible on the published site. Each morning, unlock the
# next day by force-adding it (git ignores it by default, so a plain
# `git add .` won't pick it up):
#
#   git add -f day3.html && git commit -m "Unlock Day 3" && git push
#
# Or just delete the matching line below once that day is ready to stay
# public permanently.
day3.html
day4.html
day5.html
